A documentary, a ‘transmedia platform’ and a humanitarian project: in [‘La
Furgo-Nana’](http://www.furgonana.com/en/la-furgo-nana/la-ruta/) (“a
Volkswagen Type II Bus from 1969″) Maria and Anton are driving through the Pan
American highway from [Tijuana, Mexico](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tijuana)
to [Ushuaia, Argentina](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ushuaia) to “transform
the difficult reality of Latin American children into a fascinating adventure
you will not want to miss.” Follow their
[blog](http://www.furgonana.com/category/posts/) [es], and their
[Twitter](http://twitter.com/#!/furgonana/) and
[Facebook](http://www.facebook.com/furgonana) feeds as they open our eyes to
children's rights violations and collect lullabies across the region.

